A man suffered minor injuries in Laudium after a fire broke out early Monday morning, reports the Centurion Rekord.According to Laudium Disaster Management, the man was in the building when the fire broke out in an outside building of home in 11th Avenue. The resident suffered minor burns, they said.Tshwane Emergency Services and Laudium Disaster Management responded to the scene.The cause of the fire is unknown and will form part of the investigation. Caxton News ServiceRead original story on rekordcenturion.co.za